### 123.

<span id="page_74">p. 74</span>

<span id="img_v107400"></span> ![](img/v107400.jpg)

<span class="margnote"> Of the various kinds of shadows.
(123-125).</span>Darkness is absence of light. Shadow is diminution of
light. Primitive shadow is that which is inseparable from a body not in
the light. Derived shadow is that which is disengaged from a body in
shadow and pervades the air. A cast transparent shadow is that which is
surrounded by an illuminated surface. A simple shadow is one which
receives no light from the luminous body which causes it. A simple
shadow begins within the line which starts from the edge of the luminous
body *a b*.

